<br>
         When I created Cronadan back in January, I purposely made him agnostic and neutral evil (the closest to true neutral that the game would allow).  I knew that at some point, I wanted Cronadan to break away from what was typical Teir'dal behavior.  The alignment restrictions made it difficult for him to hunt with some people, but I welcomed the challenge.  Cron's life was designed to be difficult.  The alignment restrictions coupled with the fact that he is Teir'dal made roleplaying him MUCH more challenging.  Unlike most characters I have had in the past, there was room for this one to grow.  Whether the alignment restrictions were in place or not, I would have followed the same course.<br>
<br>
       From the beginning, I roleplayed the difficulties presented to me as a Teir'dal who walked away from his people.  Uinin, Isharra and Siava are some of Cron's closest friends, but alignment restrictions, and good roleplaying made it difficult to forge these friendships before May 8th.  After May 8th, I went out of my way to roleplay these difficulties, rather than rely on game mechanics.  Since then, Lasgalen (the character) has confronted Cronadan a few times, usually resulting in an argument of some sort.  Shintou has made several death threats to Cron for betraying his people.  I take it in stride because the players behind these characters take the time to roleplay their alignments whether they are in place gamewise or not.<br>
<br>
      I have heard others say that characters like mine are a dime a dozen now.  I agree.  Everyone wants to be unique in some way.  However, unlike many so called &quot;good&quot; Dark Elves, Cronadan totally destroyed his faction in Neriak.  As a player, I took great pains to faction farm in every &quot;good&quot; city that I could.  I am 47th level, and I STILL spend a majority of my time faction farming.  Yes it is tedious, but it is true to character.  I know there are other DarkElves out there who are doing pretty much the same thing as I am.  I'm sure the other &quot;renegade&quot; Teir'dal face the same adversity that Cronadan does, or did before he became well known.  The difference is, without alignment restrictions, it makes the life of a renegade a little easier.  I know how difficult it is in proving yourself to a skeptical, and in some cases, a hostile crowd.  I love the challenge.  That is why Cronadan still exists.<br>
<br>
      Everytime this topic comes up, Cronadan is mentioned at some point, but I rarely post.  I am not one to draw attention to myself.  Still,  I just wanted everyone to know that my character actually took the time to work the game mechanics, past and present, to truly become one of those who &quot;stepped out of the box.&quot;  Roleplaying is very important to me, and I will continue to do it till this server becomes just like any other blue server.  I have been here for almost a year now, and I some of the changes that have taken place recently damaged the roleplaying environment to some degree.  Still, there are many of us left, who play the game the way that is was played from the beginning.  Fear not.  We are out there.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
